Growth improved across the board despite a guide that assumed deterioration in the spend env. With the AI Search opportunity progressing, the security business is finding its stride creating a 1- 2 punch that paves the way for further revisions against a conservative FY26 guide. Remain OW.

- Q1 total revenue growth of \(18\%\) cc was ahead of consensus and represents an acceleration from \(+16\%\) cc growth in Q4- Elastic Cloud growth improved to \(+24\%\) cc \((24.5\% \text{USD})\) , from \(+23\%\) YoY cc in Q4- AI Search opportunity making steady progress as 2,200 customer now use Elastic for Gen AI up, from 2,000 in Q4- Security was strong in Q2, fueled by the SIEM replacement opportunity, which could emerge as powerful driver of growth to go alongside Search- While FY26 revenue guidance was raised to \(+14\%\) cc vs. cons at \(+12\%\) , it still screens conservatively given implied deceleration with price increases taking effect

Is the Growth Opportunity Broadening at Elastic? When new CFO Navam Welihindaook over the role in 4Q25, he explained the initial FY26 outlook (which was mostly below consensus expectations), as a function of his desire to add an extra layer of conservatism given that he was new to the role. The key assumption was that the Fed weakness seen last quarter would spread to the enterprise/ commercial business despite little evidence of this occurring in FQ4. That assumption did prove conservative in FQ1, as growth modestly accelerated across the board - cc total revenue growth improved to \(+18\%\) YoY from \(+16\%\) in FQ4, cc subscription revenue accelerated to \(+19\%\) YoY from \(+17\%\) cc, sales-led subscription revenue (subscription - monthly cloud customer revenue) grew \(+20\% +\) cc (from \(+19\%\) cc in F425) and cc Elastic Cloud revenue grew \(+24\%\) YoY versus \(+23\%\) last

quarter. We came away with 3 major themes on the earnings call. 1) AI Search Momentum Continues to Build – the company now has 2,200 customers using Elastic for Gen AI use cases (up from 2,000 in FQ4) and of these, 330 are spending \(\) 100K+(up from 310 in FQ4). In addition, the company added more\) \ \(1+\) million Elastic Cloud customers using Elastic for Gen AI use cases than the prior two quarters combined. 2) The Security Business is Benefitting from SIEM
Elastic Cloud customers using Elastic for Gen AI use cases than the prior two quarters combined. 2) The Security Business is Benefitting from SIEM

Displacement Opportunities – the security business performed well in FQ1 reflecting, growing success in displacing incumbents with its unified SIEM/XDR solution. Management highlighted that a third of the company's new and expansion wins in the quarter involved competitive displacements. 3) The Federal Business is Stabilizing – and management expects Federal to be a compelling vertical over the mid- term. Taking a step back, our OW thesis was largely predicated on our enthusiasm for growth in the Search business to structurally improve on the back of the AI Search opportunity. We see progress on that front and but believe the transformation will play out over years, not a couple quarters. Against that reality, we are encouraged that there is renewed momentum in the Security business with the SIEM displacement opportunity. Should a 1- 2 punch of AI Search and SIEM Displacement provide durable vectors of growth, we become more confident that further upward estimate revisions are in the cards given the backdrop of conservative FY26 guidance and out- year consensus estimates.

Growth. Management raised guided FY26 revenue to \(\) 1,679-\ \(1,689\) million (from \(\) 1,655-\ \(1,670 million) implying YoY growth of +13- 14\%\) on a reported basis (+13% on a cc basis at the midpoint from 11% prior). This was ahead of MSE/Cons to \(\) 1,673/\(\) 1,666 million. Outlook for margins were held steady at 16% – inline with consensus. For Q2, management guided Q2 revenue to\) \ \(415- \) 417 million, implying +14% YoY in cc and ahead of MSE/cons of \(\) 414/\(\) 410 million. We see the current outlook as poised for further material upward revisions given:1) a 5% price increase on the entire product portfolio that went to effect in May, 2) further indications in FQ1 of a stable (versus the assumption of deteriorating) spend environment and 3) Q2 guidance which implies hardly any sequential growth despite a history of positive QoQ seasonality for both Elastic Cloud and the self- managed business.

Remain OW and Raise PIT to \(\) 120\(. Despite a strong after- hours move, we remain OW shares of Elastic given: 1) continued progress with the AI Search opportunity which will emerge as a steady driver of durable growth over the next several years, 2) the potential for the Security business to contribute more meaningfully to the growth equation with the SIEM replacement opportunity, 3) FY26 guidance which screens conservative and is poised for further upward revisions and 4) an attractive valuation with shares trading at 5.9x CY26 sales, (0.44x growth adjusted vs. infra pegs at 0.48x) and 29x CY26 FCF (1.48x growth adjusted).
